    <stitle>BRAKE COMPONENTS: This Service Manual Section should be used for reference only. For more current service
        information on all components go to the Bendix website from the ISIS Suppliers menu and refer to the Service
        Data Sheets. - MODULAR CONTROL VALVE (MV-3) - INSTALL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>INSTALL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a non-hardening sealing compound to fittings. Assemble fittings in rear of valve. Do
                not assume that the fittings will seal themselves to the body. Tighten to 120 in-lbs. (14 N&#183;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble valve to instrument panel.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect air lines to their respective fittings (refer to
                <hotlnk document="s04002r_90.xml" xrefid="f0400240">Figure 40</hotlnk>
                for porting designation).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the identification tags.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After installing the valve in the vehicle, repeat the
                <hotlnk document="s04002r_HL0400217.xml" xrefid="hl0400217">
                    <xref refid="hl0400217"/>SERVICE CHECKS
                </hotlnk>
                . Test drive the vehicle at slow speed in a safe area prior to placing back into service.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">After checking the serviceability of valve, reinstall instrument panel access cover (if
                applicable).
            </para>
        </step1>
